dp:ML_Personalization_Team a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Agent,
        prov:Entity,
        prov:Organization,
        dp:Data_Product_Team ;
    rdfs:label "ML Personalization Team"@en ;
    dctm:description """The ML Personalization Team builds and maintains recommendation and ranking models that depend on high-quality behavioral signals. Their primary concern is that model features remain stable and interpretable across time, which makes them sensitive to data schema changes, silent drops in event volume, and shifts in business logic.

In the StreamForge catalog, this team is referenced when explaining how user-level playback events and creator metadata flow into feature pipelines. They also provide good material for RAG because they connect governance concerns (privacy, retention, policy constraints) with graph lineage (datasets → activities → model artifacts) and with text-heavy model documentation."""@en ;
    skos:definition "A machine learning team responsible for personalization models that use StreamForge engagement data to drive ranking and recommendations."@en ;
    skos:editorialNote "Added to support RAG questions about personalization dependencies and feature/lineage explanations."@en ;
    skos:note "A machine learning team responsible for personalization models that use StreamForge engagement data to drive ranking and recommendations."@en,
        "Added to support RAG questions about personalization dependencies and feature/lineage explanations."@en,
        "Synthetic example data for StreamForge."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note """ML Personalization Team is an instance of Data Product Team.
ML Personalization Team is an instance of Organization.
ML Personalization Team has description The ML Personalization Team builds and maintains recommendation and ranking models that depend on high-quality behavioral signals. Their primary concern is that model features remain stable and interpretable across time, which makes them sensitive to data schema changes, silent drops in event volume, and shifts in business logic.

In the StreamForge catalog, this team is referenced when explaining how user-level playback events and creator metadata flow into feature pipelines. They also provide good material for RAG because they connect governance concerns (privacy, retention, policy constraints) with graph lineage (datasets → activities → model artifacts) and with text-heavy model documentation.
ML Personalization Team has definition A machine learning team responsible for personalization models that use StreamForge engagement data to drive ranking and recommendations."""@en ;
    dp:owns sf:Recommendation_Features_Data_Product .

