dp:Growth_Analytics_Team a owl:NamedIndividual,
        prov:Agent,
        prov:Entity,
        prov:Organization,
        dp:Data_Product_Team ;
    rdfs:label "Growth Analytics Team"@en ;
    dctm:description """The Growth Analytics Team translates raw engagement signals into actionable growth metrics used by product leadership. They define KPI semantics, validate computation logic, and ensure that metric definitions remain consistent as upstream pipelines evolve.

In the StreamForge data catalog, this team is often referenced when asking questions such as which upstream datasets influence an executive metric, which pipelines compute the metric, and how changes in definitions affect trend interpretation. Their work benefits from both text-heavy documentation (metric definitions, caveats, reporting windows) and graph-heavy lineage (what datasets and activities generate the metric snapshots)."""@en ;
    skos:definition "A team responsible for defining, computing, and interpreting growth-related KPIs for StreamForge creators and users."@en ;
    skos:editorialNote "Designed to support RAG questions about KPI definitions, computation runs, and executive dashboards."@en ;
    skos:note "A team responsible for defining, computing, and interpreting growth-related KPIs for StreamForge creators and users."@en,
        "Designed to support RAG questions about KPI definitions, computation runs, and executive dashboards."@en,
        "Synthetic example data for StreamForge."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note """Growth Analytics Team is an instance of Data Product Team.
Growth Analytics Team is an instance of Organization.
Growth Analytics Team has description The Growth Analytics Team translates raw engagement signals into actionable growth metrics used by product leadership. They define KPI semantics, validate computation logic, and ensure that metric definitions remain consistent as upstream pipelines evolve.

In the StreamForge data catalog, this team is often referenced when asking questions such as which upstream datasets influence an executive metric, which pipelines compute the metric, and how changes in definitions affect trend interpretation. Their work benefits from both text-heavy documentation (metric definitions, caveats, reporting windows) and graph-heavy lineage (what datasets and activities generate the metric snapshots).
Growth Analytics Team has definition A team responsible for defining, computing, and interpreting growth-related KPIs for StreamForge creators and users."""@en ;
    dp:owns sf:Customer_Profile_Data_Product,
        sf:User_Data_Product .

