    dp:embedding_note """Sidecar has definition A data product sidecar is a process that shares the execution context of a data product and is only responsible for domain-agnostic and cross-cutting concerns such as policy execution. In addition to policy execution, the sidecar process can be extended to implement other standardized features of a data product such as discovery. Dehghani, Zhamak. Data Mesh: Delivering Data-Driven Value at Scale (p. 4). O'Reilly Media. Kindle Edition.
Sidecar has definition Sidecars provide a convenient architectural location for enforcing semantic constraints, turning models and validation rules into executable components attached to data products."""@en .

