dp:Governance_Annotation a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Governance Annotation" ;
    rdfs:subClassOf owl:Thing,
        prov:Entity,
        dp:Governance_Annotation ;
    owl:equivalentClass dp:Governance_Annotation ;
    skos:definition "A collaborative governance overlay in which users, stewards, security teams, and automated processes can attach structured governance annotations to a data product. These annotations are distinct from the core semantic model. They capture usage context, business value, quality concerns, and risk signals, while PROV records their provenance and ODRL can represent any resulting obligations, permissions, or restrictions."@en ;
    skos:note "A collaborative governance overlay in which users, stewards, security teams, and automated processes can attach structured governance annotations to a data product. These annotations are distinct from the core semantic model. They capture usage context, business value, quality concerns, and risk signals, while PROV records their provenance and ODRL can represent any resulting obligations, permissions, or restrictions."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note """Governance Annotation is a kind of Entity.
