dp:Bounded_Context a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:label "Bounded Context"@en ;
    dctm:contributor "Michael DeBellis" ;
    dctm:created "2025-12-12T04:24:48+00:00"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:comment "A coherent domain model boundary in the sense of Domain-Driven Design."@en,
        "Data Product usage: Bounded contexts scope the semantics and meaning of Data Products and help manage dependencies between products owned by different domains."@en ;
    rdfs:subClassOf owl:Thing,
        dp:Bounded_Context ;
    owl:equivalentClass dp:Bounded_Context ;
    skos:definition "A bounded context defines the boundary within which a particular domain model and vocabulary apply."@en,
        "Bounded Context is a concept from Domain-Driven Design (DDD) that defines a clear boundary within which a particular domain model, vocabulary, and set of assumptions are valid and consistently used. Within a bounded context, terms have precise meanings and models are internally coherent, while the same terms may have different meanings in other contexts. By explicitly defining these boundaries, bounded contexts reduce ambiguity, limit coupling between systems, and enable teams to evolve models independently while integrating with other contexts through well-defined interfaces or translation mechanisms."@en ;
    skos:note "A bounded context defines the boundary within which a particular domain model and vocabulary apply."@en,
        "Bounded Context is a concept from Domain-Driven Design (DDD) that defines a clear boundary within which a particular domain model, vocabulary, and set of assumptions are valid and consistently used. Within a bounded context, terms have precise meanings and models are internally coherent, while the same terms may have different meanings in other contexts. By explicitly defining these boundaries, bounded contexts reduce ambiguity, limit coupling between systems, and enable teams to evolve models independently while integrating with other contexts through well-defined interfaces or translation mechanisms."@en ;
    dp:embedding_note """Bounded Context is a kind of Bounded Context.
owl:Nothing is a kind of Bounded Context.
Bounded Context has comment A coherent domain model boundary in the sense of Domain-Driven Design.
Bounded Context has comment Data Product usage: Bounded contexts scope the semantics and meaning of Data Products and help manage dependencies between products owned by different domains.
Bounded Context has definition A bounded context defines the boundary within which a particular domain model and vocabulary apply.
Bounded Context has definition Bounded Context is a concept from Domain-Driven Design (DDD) that defines a clear boundary within which a particular domain model, vocabulary, and set of assumptions are valid and consistently used. Within a bounded context, terms have precise meanings and models are internally coherent, while the same terms may have different meanings in other contexts. By explicitly defining these boundaries, bounded contexts reduce ambiguity, limit coupling between systems, and enable teams to evolve models independently while integrating with other contexts through well-defined interfaces or translation mechanisms."""@en .

